<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-057-134 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 316 989</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Sept 19 1991* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>ATandamp;T announces cause of service outage. (ATandamp;T announces thatSeptember 17, 1991 outage in New York was caused by apower-conserving program)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Blankenhorn, Dana.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   American Telephone and Telegraph Co. (Accidents).andO;Ticker:    T.andO;Topic:     Power SupplyTelephone companiesTelecommunications Services.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>****ATandamp;T ANNOUNCES CAUSE OF SERVICE OUTAGE 09/19/91 NEW YORK, NEW YORK,U.S.A., 1991 SEP 19 (NB) -- A program to conserve power was apparently behindthe September 17 collapse of 2 ATandamp;T switches in Lower Manhattan whichdisrupted phone service for six hours and left thousands of air travelersstranded.andP;  Chairman Robert E. Allen and communications president Victor A.andO;Pelson were said to have been personally involved in tracking down theproblem.andM;In a statement released at mid-afternoon on September 18, ATandamp;T laid out whathappened.andP;  The use of square brackets is Newsbytes' definitions of thetechnologies or entities named and was not a part of the original statement.andM;&quot;At approximately 10 AM on Tuesday, September 17, in cooperation with ConEdison andlsqb;the local power companyandrsqb;, ATandamp;T activated a power sharing plan in anATandamp;T switching center in lower Manhattan, a routine practice that assists inenergy conservation.andP;  At such times, ATandamp;T leaves commercial power andoperates on its own internally generated power.andM;&quot;During or after that cutover to internal power, critical power rectifiersandlsqb;which change AC power to DCandrsqb; failed, for reasons that are beinginvestigated.andP;  Power was provided by a battery back-up system designed tooperate for six hours.andP;  ATandamp;T is still determining why alarm proceduresdesigned to warn that the power system was functioning on back-up batterypower failed to work.andM;&quot;At approximately 4:30 PM, the shift back to commercial power was attempted.andO;This cutover did not take place due to the prior failure of the powerrectifiers.andP;  Service was affected as battery life expired.&quot; The statementcontinued that ATandamp;T has begun putting $200 million into improvements in itspower supplies and other critical back-up systems, which will greatly reducethe risk of similar problems in the future.andP;  ATandamp;T said it has spent $18billion modernizing its network over the last seven years.andM;The New York service outage was ATandamp;T's third in less than two years --previous problems involved computer software and a cable cut.andP;  It came justas the company was announcing a range of new products, including cellularphones, but news of the cut buried most of that news.andM;(Dana Blankenhorn/19910919/Press Contact: Bob Nersesian, ATandamp;T, 908-221-2305)</TEXT></DOC>